data.name: Domino Specialty Ingredients
data.description: Domino Specialty Ingredients offers an extended array of innovative Sweetener Solutions and Rice Products.

data.name: Nulomoline
data.description: Standardized inverts made from pure cane sugar by a process that converts sucrose into a combination of fructose and dextrose sugars, resulting in a characteristically unique sweetener system. These sugars have significantly different characteristics than sucrose, corn syrup combinations, or other sugars, and offer a lighter flavor, increased moisture retention in fresh baked goods, improved crust color, solubility, and enhanced shelf life. FreshVert® Liquid and Nulomoline® #7 are liquid forms, FreshVert® Creamy and Nulomoline® Congealed are high-solids forms, and Nulomoline® #11 is a partial-invert liquid form.

data.name: Easy Fond
data.description: A dry candy fondant produced by taking micron-sized crystals of pure cane sugar, bonding them with invert sugar to create porous, free-flowing white particles that are naturally resistant to caking. Just add water (no heat) to produce the highest quality fondant for candy products with excellent extrusion qualities and superior whiteness and taste. This convenient method disperses fats, oils, colors, flavors and emulsifiers; resulting in no separation, grit, or clumping texture in your cream centers, caramels, cordials, fudge and glazes.

data.name: Bakers Drivert
data.description: A dry baking fondant manufactured to the highest standards. Micron-sized crystals of pure cane sugar have been bonded with invert sugar to produce porous, free-flowing white particles resistant to caking, grain or grit. Bakers Drivert®; has no added anti-caking agents and merely requires the addition of water (with no heat) to produce the highest quality fondant for icings, glazes and pan-coated confections. It acts as a dispersing medium for fats, oils and emulsifiers with excellent extrusion qualities and superior whiteness and taste. Natural humectants keep icing moist and provide longer shelf life.

data.name: FreshVert
data.description: Standardized inverts made from pure cane sugar by a process that converts sucrose into a combination of fructose and dextrose sugars, resulting in a characteristically unique sweetener system. These sugars have significantly different characteristics than sucrose, corn syrup combinations, or other sugars, and offer a lighter flavor, increased moisture retention in fresh baked goods, improved crust color, solubility, and enhanced shelf life. FreshVert® Liquid and Nulomoline® #7 are liquid forms, FreshVert® Creamy and Nulomoline® Congealed are high-solids forms, and Nulomoline® #11 is a partial-invert liquid form.

data.name: Super Envision
data.description: A more concentrated extension of the Domino Specialty Ingredient Envision® co-crystallized flavor and texture modification product line. This unique heat-stable ingredient allows for the use of a full range of carbohydrates to maintain the desired attributes of products, such as moisture retention, mouth feel, and water activity. Due to its higher concentration, Super Envision® is typically used at <1% in a formulation which achieves desired results in your finished goods at a lower cost. Applications range from light sweet to savory cheese, meat, and vegetable flavors in bakery, confection, nutraceutical, prepared foods, soups, snacks, and sauces, making Super Envision® an extremely versatile and effective ingredient.

data.name: Tricol
data.description: Tricol® Syrups (light, medium) are well balanced, delicately flavored brown syrups obtained from the refining of cane sugar. The color, flavor, and aroma are designed to give the food processor flexibility to use separately or to accent sweet or savory bakery, confection, and prepared food products. The invert content has been standardized for uniform regulation of dough fermentation and shelf life extension in bakery products.

data.name: Cypha
data.description: An artificial flavor enhancer that masks the perception of sweetness in a food or beverage. Cypha™ has the ability to inhibit sweetness in various products without adding any additional calories. A variety of benefits include easy compatibility with all food ingredients, stability in thermal and baking food processes, and low pH/high acidic conditions over the entirety of a product’s shelf life. The unobtrusive nature of this product allows for its use without affecting moisture retention, mouth-feel, or water activity. Applications range from light sweet to savory cheese, meat, and vegetable flavors in bakery, confection, nutraceutical, prepared foods, soups, snacks, and sauces.

data.name: Set & Match
data.description: A high quality fondant sugar used to make smooth, creamy but textured icings and high quality glazes. This ingredient provides rapid wet-out in cold water with excellent adherence and sheen as well as extending shelf life. Its fast-drying characteristics with no separation, grit, or clumping texture result in a smooth non-cracking presentation for your finished product.

data.name: Nulomoline® (congealed or liquid)
data.description: Standardized inverts made from pure cane sugar by a process that converts sucrose into a combination of fructose and dextrose sugars, resulting in a characteristically unique sweetener system. These sugars have significantly different characteristics than sucrose, corn syrup combinations, or other sugars, and offer a lighter flavor, increased moisture retention in fresh baked goods, improved crust color, solubility, and enhanced shelf life. FreshVert® Liquid and Nulomoline® #7 are liquid forms, FreshVert® Creamy and Nulomoline® Congealed are high-solids forms, and Nulomoline® #11 is a partial-invert liquid form.

data.name: Domino Specialty Ingredients Qwik-Flo® Honey (granulated and powdered)
data.description: Made with pure honey and possessing a pure golden color and smooth flavor, the free-flowing characteristics of these instantly soluble ingredients increase handling efficiencies. Easy to blend and non-hygroscopic, their applications include bakery mixes, cereals, seasoning blends, dried soups, and beverages. These products are not of genetically modified origin and do not include any genetically engineered additives or ingredients.

data.name: Domino Specialty Ingredients LCMT - Sucrose Syrup
data.description: LCMT Medium Invert Syrup is partially inverted sugar syrup that has a pale yellow color. LCMT Medium Invert Syrup is a stable sweetening syrup with low flavor, color, metal and turbidity. It is 100% soluble and can be used in alcohol and non-alcoholic drink applications where clarity of the product is necessary. The light flavor note enhances sweet and savory products and is a shelf life extender in baked goods. LCMT Sucrose Syrup is also available in organic form.

data.name: Dri-Flo® Special 75 Molasses
data.description: A free-flowing sprayed dried ingredient with a robust flavor and dark brown caramel color. This product is manufactured by dehydrating a high quality molasses in combination with maltodextrin as a drying aid. Flow agents have not been added. This uniformly blended product is ideal for dry and liquid blending. Attributes include dispersability, solubility, and effective masking of undesirable flavors.

data.name: Millhouse® Molasses
data.description: A molasses made directly from pure cane sugar. This unsulphured rich amber brown molasses is mildly sweet and is refined through a unique process which lends a distinctive golden brown color.

data.name: Golden Granulated® Raw Cane Sugar, Certified Organic Powdered
data.description: A very fine grain baking and confectioner's sweetener with a mild sugarcane flavor. Organic raw cane sugar is ground into a fine 10X powder and blended with organic cornstarch to prevent caking that produces an off-white coloring. Organic Powdered Raw Cane Sugar adds perfect sweetness, bulk, and structure to icings, glazes, frappe, frosting, fudge, whipped creams, hard candies, and other confections.

data.name: Golden Granulated® Raw Cane Sugar, Extra Fine
data.description: An extra fine granulated, soluble, free-flowing general purpose sweetener. It retains a slight golden tan color and subtle taste profile from the cane juice that will enhance any application. The single crystallization process gives Raw Cane Sugar its attractive flavor, color and nutritional profile. It is the ideal alternative to refined white sugar.
